Package: natambio
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: jackd2 | jackd
Suggests: natambio-tools, natambio-drc
Description: real-time JACK ambiophonic / surround processor
 NatAmbio (Nat(ural) Ambio(phonics) Surround) is a real-time JACK audio client
 that chains two processing stages driven by a single XML configuration:
 .
  * NAE -- PCA-based spatial decomposition of a stereo signal into main +
    ambience (front) or a surround signal (rear), via a 2x2 covariance
    eigenvalue solver running in dedicated real-time worker threads.
  * Convolution -- per-channel partitioned FFT convolution using Fons
    Adriaensen's zita-convolver, as arbitrary routing graphs of channels.
 .
 This package contains the real-time JACK client and example configurations.

Package: natambio-tools
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends}
Description: offline FIR filter generators for NatAmbio (C tools)
 Command-line helpers that reuse NatAmbio's shared filter-design code to
 produce filters offline, outside the real-time JACK client:
 .
  * natambio-xtc-filters  -- XTC (crosstalk cancellation) FIR pair generator.
 .
 This package contains the compiled C/C++ tools.

Package: natambio-ladspa
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends}
Description: LADSPA plugin port of the NatAmbio NAE engine
 A LADSPA module implementing NatAmbio's PCA-based stereo spatial
 decomposition, so the same main/ambience separation
 can be run in any LADSPA-compatible host (e.g. ecasound) outside the JACK
 application. Useful for quick experimentation and algorithm verification.

Package: natambio-drc
Architecture: all
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 python3,
 python3-numpy,
 python3-scipy,
 python3-soundfile
Recommends: natambio-tools
Description: offline Python toolkit for NatAmbio (DRC measurement + offline NAE)
 Standalone Python utilities shipped with NatAmbio. They do not require a
 running JACK server and are exposed as namespaced commands:
 .
  * natambio-pca4drc      -- PCA decomposition of a set of impulse responses
    for digital room correction (no pyDRC dependency).
  * natambio-sweepgen     -- log-sweep excitation / inverse pair generator.
  * natambio-fft-convolve -- FFT convolution of two WAV files.
  * natambio-check-capture-- clipping / level / SNR check of a capture.
  * natambio-wav2raw / natambio-raw2wav -- WAV <-> float32 raw conversion.
  * natambio-nae          -- offline NAE (ambient extraction) over a WAV file.
 .
 The scripts and their reference data (target curves, DRC configs, microphone
 calibration files) are installed under /usr/share/natambio/.
